\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Hey, did you guys order for me? This is just how I like it!"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "No, you ordered yourself, but you went back to sleep. Your energy levels weren't high enough to maintain your awareness."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Hmm... cake's good too!" Liz spoke with her mouth full.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Paula meanwhile looked as if she were going crosseyed. Suddenly her shape flickered, rippled and then she was half leopard, half female. She appeared to be naked, but covered with short fur patterned with leopard spots. The fur faded out about the level of her breasts, though the spots continue to her neck. Her breasts were much bigger, probably D cup or even larger.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Very good paula!" nalini commented.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 She grinned saucily "Now my tits are bigger, you can admire mine!"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Yeah, but can you stop trying to be the center of attention? We're here for liz."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini commented "You'd better stare at them danny, make her happy." I did so for a minute or so. Liz was sufficiently surprised that she had stopped eating, and was sitting with her mouth half open. Nalini added "Paula, would you like us all to feel them as well? Would that make you happier? Would you like me to grow a penis and spread you here on the table?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Paula realized she was overstepping the mark. "Oh... I just didn't want liz to feel she was the odd one out.... sorry."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "All right. We love you very much paula, but we're here to explain things to liz. Can you just behave a little less outrageously?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Paula nodded, switched back to her normal self. "I might have a cake. Waiter!" she waved a hand in the air.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Liz, you obviously have questions. Ask away. We'll try to answer them all."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "I dunno where to start. How did paula do that? Where are we? How did I get here?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini continued "And is paula always like this? No, she just needs a good screw. The sooner prospero gets back the better, it'll stop her eyeing off danny."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Maybe it's full moon?..." paula started. She caught the look on nalini's face. "Sorry. I'll behave."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Good." I turned to liz. "Perhaps you should tell us what you think first, so we know where to start?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Okay, I'm dreaming, aren't I? And so are all of you." We nodded. "So where are we? How come it looks so real? How can we actually meet up?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini started "All right, all of us have 3 separate bodies, our physical, our dreaming body, and a spirit body. They are something like different octaves of the same note, if that makes sense. So you can have a C note that's low, go up an octave and have another C note that is the same, but higher."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz nodded thoughtfully. "I did some music at school."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Good. They each have their own awareness, and are capable of acting independently of each other. Most of the time we aren't even aware of this..."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz was shaking her head.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 I explained "When you are awake, that is your waking awareness, or your physical body's awareness. That is what we normally think of as ourselves. You clear so far?" Liz nodded. "Good. Now consider what happens when we go to sleep. What happens to our waking or physical awareness?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Um... I'd guess it goes to sleep. But what about when we dream?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Ah, you're on to it. Our attention is usually with our physical awareness, especially when we are awake. But when the physical body goes to sleep, the physical awareness is also asleep, or at some very low level. Our attention turns to our dreaming body, and its awareness. So right now, your physical is asleep, your attention is on your dreaming body. You can't remember how you were a little while ago, but paula commented you were acting as if you were stoned. You did things like stare at the reflections in your coffee. You kept saying the same thing over and over, because you'd forgotten you'd said it."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Really?!"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Most people are the same when they dream. Their dreaming awareness lacks energy, has never been trained the way our physical awareness has been, it's not very useful to most people. Now, we asked a guide to help us, and it boosted your energy, and opened your channel wider. You need to practice in dreaming to keep that channel open."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini continued "At the moment, your attention is focussed on your dreaming awareness. Because of your energy levels, a lot of your waking awareness has transferred itself to your dreaming body. When your energy fades, as it will later tonight, you will revert back to what you were. You should be able to remember things in waking though, because your waking awareness is present now. This is what makes the difference between dreams you can't remember or vaguely remember, and dreams you can rmemeber quite vividly. Keep doing your energy exercises, and you will improve. You should be able to find your own way here tomorrow night."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Where is here?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "It's the astral isn't it?" paula put in.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Probably." i replied. "There aren't any adequate words in english. The Astral Realm is one term, the World of Dreaming is another, and even the Spirit World. You might be more familiar with the last, this is where shamans come in trances, this is where most of the spirit beings live."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz was looking more alert now, nodding.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini continued "This world is like our dreaming body, similar to the physical world, but a higher octave. Parts of it correspond with the physical world, so you can be floating around your bedroom and see yourself asleep in bed."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "That's happened to me a couple of times. Scared the hell out of me the first time, I thought I was dying. Then my grandma told me i was in the spirit world, but where it overlaps our own, and if i was good the spirits would teach me things."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini smiled, nodded. "And she was right. Other parts of the spirit world don't overlap, some like here mimic the physical world, and other parts don't correspond at all. The guides, which we'll get to soon, are spirit beings, and they will be able to teach you things about this world. Now, there are two things you should notice about us. First, do you see swirls of color surrounding each of us?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Lis shook her head. "Nope, you look about the same as normal."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "All right, that will come later. I was going to point out that we all have auras, that's what they're called. Everyone else around here has an aura, including the guides. But the waiters do not. They are not real in the sense that you and i are real, they are a dreaming construct. For now you'll have to accept this. One day you will start to see auras and you will know what I mean.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "The spirit world, or dreaming world, can be changed by our thoughts. That was how paula changed into a leopard woman and back again. The furniture, the surroundings, even the coffee and cake are constructs." She concentrated for a moment, and several small brightly colored butterflies appeared and fluttered around paula. "I just created those butterflies."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Kewl! I guess I'l learn how to do that in due course?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Yes. Now the other thing you should notice is that each of us has a fiber or line coming out of the backs of our heads." I turned my head and she pointed out my line to liz. It's a ghostly line, something like smoke, and not always easy to see. "That is a line that connects our dreaming bodies to our physical ones. Anyone you see with such a line is a dreamer, regardless of their shape. Anyone who doesn't have such a line does not have a physical body. Some will be people who have died, while others are like the guides - they are spirit beings, they never had a physical body."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 I added "Something else about your dreaming awareness - sometimes it does intrude into waking. You know sometimes you have a sense of deja vu, or sometimes a premonition? That's your dreaming awareness intruding into waking. Meditation and some of the energy exercises help to align both awarenesses, so they cross over and support each other. This is to be encouraged. In a sense, the three awarenesses are something like the three legs of a stool. Most people spend their lives with their stool balanced on only one leg. We are learning to be different."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz smiled. "I can relate to explanations like that. I was going to ask what or where is the attention you mentioned before, the one that focusses on awareness? But I guess you'll tell me its in the seat of the stool"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 I grinned. "Very good! I'm not sure what the seat represents, something behind the three bodies, but none of us are advanced enough to know what that is. Nalini and I loosely refer to it as the soul, but we could be quite wrong. All I can say is that development is a process that takes lifetimes."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Phew!" Liz stared off into the distance for a while. "So some of these are dead people, and some are spirit beings. How can you tell the difference?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Nalini replied "That isn't always easy. The guides are those telegraph pole like things, those blue and orange puff balls are another type, they're both spirit beings. If you see a human shape, chances are it's either a dreamer or a dead person. Spirit beings don't often masquerade as humans. When you can see the aura, you'll recognize human auras even when the er... being in question is shaped differently. If it's not a human aura, then you have to use other knowledge. This region is where humans come, so if it isn't human, it probably is a spirit being. If you're somewhere else, you may have to ask. If there is a guide with you, then ask the guide. They seem to know everything."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz was looking thoughtful, puzzled. I admonished "Don't worry liz, find your way here tomorrow night, and we'll run over this again. We'll also talk to you tomorrow about what you can remember, and run through this in waking. Eventually the knowledge will stick."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz nodded. "I think I'll need you to go over it several times. But that's cool."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Paula was almost bouncing up and down in her seat. "Hey liz, aren't you going to ask the obvious question?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Uh... what's that?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "If there are dead people here, what happens when we die?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz nodded again. "Yeah, what does happen?" She looked surprised "Oh, gotta go pee!" and vanished. She had obviously woken up.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Hey guys, now she's gone, can we go look at that shadow we passed through a week ago?"}
